The paper deals with the optimization of communication load in distributed computing systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of coding techniques to reduce communication load also relates to data structures (cs.DS) and system theory (cs.SY). Finally, the optimization of data placement and shuffling involves networked systems (cs.NI).
